Desert Island Discs: Tom Daley yana da ra'ayin rashin tausayi game da jima'i
Dan wasan Olympic Tom Daley ya ce ya girma da rashin tausayi saboda jima'i - amma hakan ne ya motsa shi ya yi nasara.
Ya kasance mai shekaru 24 bai san komai ba har sai ya shiga makarantar sakandare kuma ya ji cewa ba kowa bane kamar ni.
A jawabinsa na farko a Radio 4 Desert Island Discs wanda Lauren Laverne ta gabatar, ta yi magana game da hakkin gay na ba da bege ga wasu.
Ya kuma ce bayan ya zama uba, bai da muhimmanci a lashe gasar Olympics.
Mai gabatar da shirin da aka yi a wannan shirin, Kris Young ya yi hutu na watanni da yawa saboda rashin lafiya.
Da ya bayyana a cikin shirin farko na Laverne, Daley ya ce ya ji kasa da 'yan uwansa a lokacin da yake girma saboda ba a yarda da shi a matsayin namiji ko mace.
Ya ce: "Har zuwa yau, rashin jin dadin mutane da kuma rashin jin dadin mutane sune abubuwan da suka motsa ni kuma suka ba ni karfin yin nasara.
Ta so ta tabbatar da cewa ita ce ta ce, don haka ba ta yi wa kowa laifi ba idan sun san game da jima'i.
Wannan dan wasan da ya lashe lambar tagulla a gasar Olympics sau biyu yanzu yana da babban matsayi wanda ke yin gwagwarmaya ga 'yan LBGT kuma ya yi amfani da bayyanarsa a Wasannin Commonwealth a Ostiraliya a wannan shekara don ƙarin ƙasashe su daina yin cin zarafin jima'i.
